AIM:
The goal of this is to do some simple examination of data and make charts in Python, using Pandas, Matplotlib and Seaborn. We'll do this with functions like info(), sum(), describe(), removing copies of rows, a histogram, a boxplot, a scatterplot and then save the data as a CSV file. 


Algorithm:
Start the program.
Import pandas, matplotlib.pyplot, and seaborn modules.
Create a sample dataframe.
Display dataframe information using info().
Find column-wise sum using sum().
Remove duplicate rows using drop_duplicates().
Display statistical summary using describe().
Plot histogram using hist().
Plot boxplot using seaborn.
Plot scatterplot using seaborn.
Export dataframe to CSV file.
Display outputs and stop the program.

SOURCE CODE:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Sample dataframe
data = {
    "Sex": ["male", "male", "female"],
    "Age": [22, 38, 26],
    "SibSp": [1, 1, 0],
    "Parch": [0, 0, 0],
    "Fare": [7.25, 71.83, 7.92]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Display information
print(df.info())

# Sum of columns
print(df.sum(numeric_only=True))

# Remove duplicates
df = df.drop_duplicates(inplace=False)

# Statistical description
print(df.describe())

# Histogram
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
plt.suptitle("Histogram")
df.hist()
plt.show()

# Boxplot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.boxplot(data=df)
plt.title("Boxplot")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

# Scatterplot
sns.pairplot(df)
plt.show()

# Export to CSV
df.to_csv("cleaned_data.csv", index=False)

print("CSV file created successfully")


